HEADWORD: Mechanographic
<hw>Mech`an*o*graph`ic</hw>
<pr>(m⟦ecr⟧k`⟦ait⟧n*⟦osl⟧*gr⟦acr⟧f"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Treating of mechanics.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Written, copied, or recorded by machinery; produced
by mechanography; <as>as, a <ex>mechanographic</ex> record of changes of
temperature; <ex>mechanographic</ex> prints.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mechanographist</ent>⟦br⟧
